snippet: Derick Brassard scored a power-play goal 1:50 into overtime, after Detroit tied it in the closing seconds of regulation, to give the New York Rangers their fifth straight victory over the Red Wings, 4-3 on Wednesday night....

headline.print_headline: Brassard's OT Goal Lifts Rangers Over Red Wings
headline.main: Brassard's OT Goal Lifts Rangers Over Red Wings

lead_paragraph: Derick Brassard scored a power-play goal 1:50 into overtime, after Detroit tied it in the closing seconds of regulation, to give the New York Rangers their fifth straight victory over the Red Wings, 4-3 on Wednesday night.
